race.comment: ASTON GOLEA (2) missed the frame last time, finishing 7th (23.10) last time in a Rank Limit - Grade 5 at Geelong. Has won here at this journey. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. HARD COMPASS (4) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by a neck at Shepparton in a handy 25.81 beating Miss Black. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. One of the key runners again. AKELA YOUNG (1) turned in a plain performance last time when sixth at this track over 425m behind Frank Grimes (24.87) in a Bottom Up - Grade 5. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. WHITE SHIRAZ (7) is worth including.
